<br>
I just saw this wonderful image by Polykarbon over at BoardDreams.com:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.boarddreams.com/images/newskater.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <br>
<br>
So how'd he get those lines on the skateboarder so perfectly thick? I know I could scan in an image (without those thick lines) and manually thicken all of those lines in Illustrator (very tedious) but I don't think that's how it was done. Was it originally scanned with those lines inked that thick and then cleaned up in Streamline? I'm not sure if that's true either because they look so dang perfect. Any ideas? I'm wondering if maybe there's some shortcut in Illustrator that I'm not aware of....<br>
<br>
Any suggestions are greatly appreciated!<br>
<br>
